Quickstrike:





Quickstrike grabbed Dark Mouse's tail before she did anything else. She 
pulled her back away from the vent. "Better let me go first," he said. 
"These tin-horns pack uh mighty punch. They don't like it when bots mess 
wit' the main computer." He chuckled lightly.

He shouldered his way past Dark Mouse, putting the left bunch of walking 
legs against the air vent wall. He paused and looked at the room through the 
vent.
